label: agent
desc: An agent (eg. person, group, software or physical artifact).

label: document
desc: A document.

label: group
desc: A class of Agents.

label: image
desc: An image.

label: label property
desc: A foaf:LabelProperty is any RDF property with texual values that serve as labels.

label: online account
desc: An online account.

label: online chat account
desc: An online chat account.

label: online e-commerce account
desc: An online e-commerce account.

label: online gaming account
desc: An online gaming account.

label: organization
desc: An organization.

label: person
desc: A person.

label: personalprofiledocument
desc: A personal profile RDF document.

label: project
desc: A project (a collective endeavour of some kind).

label: account
desc: Indicates an account held by this agent.

label: account
desc: Indicates an account held by this agent.

label: account name
desc: Indicates the name (identifier) associated with this online account.

label: account service homepage
desc: Indicates a homepage of the service provide for this online account.

label: age
desc: The age in years of some agent.

label: aim chat id
desc: An AIM chat ID

label: based near
desc: A location that something is based near, for some broadly human notion of near.

label: birthday
desc: The birthday of this Agent, represented in mm-dd string form, eg. '12-31'.

label: current project
desc: A current project this person works on.

label: depiction
desc: A depiction of some thing.

label: depicts
desc: A thing depicted in this representation.

label: dna checksum
desc: A checksum for the DNA of some thing. Joke.

label: familyname
desc: The family name of some person.

label: family_name
desc: The family name of some person.

label: firstname
desc: The first name of a person.

label: focus
desc: The underlying or 'focal' entity associated with some SKOS-described concept.

label: funded by
desc: An organization funding a project or person.

label: geekcode
desc: A textual geekcode for this person, see http://www.geekcode.com/geek.html

label: gender
desc: The gender of this Agent (typically but not necessarily 'male' or 'female').

label: given name
desc: The given name of some person.

label: given name
desc: The given name of some person.

label: homepage
desc: A homepage for some thing.

label: icq chat id
desc: An ICQ chat ID

label: image
desc: An image that can be used to represent some thing (ie. those depictions which are particularly representative of something, eg. one's photo on a homepage).

label: interest
desc: A page about a topic of interest to this person.

label: is primary topic of
desc: A document that this thing is the primary topic of.

label: jabber id
desc: A jabber ID for something.

label: knows
desc: A person known by this person (indicating some level of reciprocated interaction between the parties).

label: lastname
desc: The last name of a person.

label: logo
desc: A logo representing some thing.

label: made
desc: Something that was made by this agent.

label: maker
desc: An agent that made this thing.

label: personal mailbox
desc: A personal mailbox, ie. an Internet mailbox associated with exactly one owner, the first owner of this mailbox. This is a 'static inverse functional property', in that there is (across time and change) at most one individual that ever has any particular value for foaf:mbox.

label: sha1sum of a personal mailbox uri name
desc: The sha1sum of the URI of an Internet mailbox associated with exactly one owner, the first owner of the mailbox.

label: member
desc: Indicates a member of a Group

label: membershipclass
desc: Indicates the class of individuals that are a member of a Group

label: msn chat id
desc: An MSN chat ID

label: myersbriggs
desc: A Myers Briggs (MBTI) personality classification.

label: name
desc: A name for some thing.

label: nickname
desc: A short informal nickname characterising an agent (includes login identifiers, IRC and other chat nicknames).

label: openid
desc: An OpenID for an Agent.

label: page
desc: A page or document about this thing.

label: past project
desc: A project this person has previously worked on.

label: phone
desc: A phone, specified using fully qualified tel: URI scheme (refs: http://www.w3.org/Addressing/schemes.html#tel).

label: plan
desc: A .plan comment, in the tradition of finger and '.plan' files.

label: primary topic
desc: The primary topic of some page or document.

label: publications
desc: A link to the publications of this person.

label: schoolhomepage
desc: A homepage of a school attended by the person.

label: sha1sum (hex)
desc: A sha1sum hash, in hex.

label: skype id
desc: A Skype ID

label: status
desc: A string expressing what the user is happy for the general public (normally) to know about their current activity.

label: surname
desc: The surname of some person.

label: theme
desc: A theme.

label: thumbnail
desc: A derived thumbnail image.

label: tipjar
desc: A tipjar document for this agent, describing means for payment and reward.

label: title
desc: Title (Mr, Mrs, Ms, Dr. etc)

label: topic
desc: A topic of some page or document.

label: topic_interest
desc: A thing of interest to this person.

label: weblog
desc: A weblog of some thing (whether person, group, company etc.).

label: work info homepage
desc: A work info homepage of some person; a page about their work for some organization.

label: workplace homepage
desc: A workplace homepage of some person; the homepage of an organization they work for.

label: yahoo chat id
desc: A Yahoo chat ID

label: affirmedby
desc: A legal decision that affirms a ruling.

label: annotates
desc: Critical or explanatory note for a Document.

label: list of authors
desc: An ordered list of authors. Normally, this list is seen as a priority list that order authors by importance.

label: cited by
desc:
Relates a document to another document that cites the
first document.

label: cites
desc:
Relates a document to another document that is cited
by the first document as reference, comment, review, quotation or for
another purpose.

label: list of contributors
desc: An ordered list of contributors. Normally, this list is seen as a priority list that order contributors by importance.

label: court
desc: A court associated with a legal document; for example, that which issues a decision.

label: degree
desc: The thesis degree.

label: director
desc: A Film director.

label: distributor
desc: Distributor of a document or a collection of documents.

label: editor
desc: A person having managerial and sometimes policy-making responsibility for the editorial part of a publishing firm or of a newspaper, magazine, or other publication.

label: list of editors
desc: An ordered list of editors. Normally, this list is seen as a priority list that order editors by importance.

label: interviewee
desc: An agent that is interviewed by another agent.

label: interviewer
desc: An agent that interview another agent.

label: issuer
desc: An entity responsible for issuing often informally published documents such as press releases, reports, etc.

label: organizer
desc: The organizer of an event; includes conference organizers, but also government agencies or other bodies that are responsible for conducting hearings.

label: owner
desc: Owner of a document or a collection of documents.

label: presented at
desc: Relates a document to an event; for example, a paper to a conference.

label: presents
desc: Relates an event to associated documents; for example, conference to a paper.

label: producer
desc: Producer of a document or a collection of documents.

label: recipient
desc: An agent that receives a communication document.

label: reproducedin
desc: The resource in which another resource is reproduced.

label: reversedby
desc: A legal decision that reverses a ruling.

label: review of
desc: Relates a review document to a reviewed thing (resource, item, etc.).

label: status
desc: The publication status of (typically academic) content.

label: subsequentlegaldecision
desc: A legal decision on appeal that takes action on a case (affirming it, reversing it, etc.).

label: transcript of
desc: Relates a document to some transcribed original.

label: translation of
desc: Relates a translated document to the original document.

label: translator
desc: A person who translates written document from one language to another.

label: abstract
desc: A summary of the resource.

label: date argued
desc: The date on which a legal case is argued before a court. Date is of format xsd:date

label: chapter
desc: An chapter number

label: content
desc: This property is for a plain-text rendering of the content of a Document. While the plain-text content of an entire document could be described by this property.

label: edition
desc: The name defining a special edition of a document. Normally its a literal value composed of a version number and words.

label: issue
desc: An issue number

label: locator
desc: A description (often numeric) that locates an item within a containing document or collection.

label: number of pages
desc: The number of pages contained in a document

label: number of volumes
desc: The number of volumes contained in a collection of documents (usually a series, periodical, etc.).

label: number
desc: A generic item or document number. Not to be confused with issue number.

label: page end
desc: Ending page number within a continuous page range.

label: page start
desc: Starting page number within a continuous page range.

label: pages
desc: A string of non-contiguous page spans that locate a Document within a Collection. Example: 23-25, 34, 54-56. For continuous page ranges, use the pageStart and pageEnd properties.

label: prefix name
desc: The prefix of a name

label: section
desc: A section number

label: short title
desc: The abbreviation of a title.

label: suffix name
desc: The suffix of a name

label: uri
desc: Universal Resource Identifier of a document

label: volume
desc: A volume number

label: academic article
desc: A scholarly academic article, typically published in a journal.

label: article
desc: A written composition in prose, usually nonfiction, on a specific topic, forming an independent part of a book or other publication, as a newspaper or magazine.

label: audio document
desc: An audio document; aka record.

label: audio-visual document
desc: An audio-visual document; film, video, and so forth.

label: bill
desc: Draft legislation presented for discussion to a legal body.

label: book
desc: A written or printed work of fiction or nonfiction, usually on sheets of paper fastened or bound together within covers.

label: book section
desc: A section of a book.

label: brief
desc: A written argument submitted to a court.

label: chapter
desc: A chapter of a book.

label: code
desc: A collection of statutes.

label: collected document
desc: A document that simultaneously contains other documents.

label: collection
desc: A collection of Documents or Collections

label: conference
desc: A meeting for consultation or discussion.

label: court reporter
desc: A collection of legal cases.

label: document
desc: A document (noun) is a bounded physical representation of body of information designed with the capacity (and usually intent) to communicate. A document may manifest symbolic, diagrammatic or sensory-representational information.

label: document part
desc: a distinct part of a larger document or collected document.

label: document status
desc: The status of the publication of a document.

label: edited book
desc: An edited book.

label: email
desc: A written communication addressed to a person or organization and transmitted electronically.

label: excerpt
desc: A passage selected from a larger work.

label: film
desc: aka movie.

label: hearing
desc: An instance or a session in which testimony and arguments are presented, esp. before an official, as a judge in a lawsuit.

label: image
desc: A document that presents visual or diagrammatic information.

label: interview
desc: A formalized discussion between two or more people.

label: issue
desc: something that is printed or published and distributed, esp. a given number of a periodical

label: journal
desc: A periodical of scholarly journal Articles.

label: legal case document
desc: A document accompanying a legal case.

label: decision
desc: A document containing an authoritative determination (as a decree or judgment) made after consideration of facts or law.

label: legal document
desc: A legal document; for example, a court decision, a brief, and so forth.

label: legislation
desc: A legal document proposing or enacting a law or a group of laws.

label: letter
desc: A written or printed communication addressed to a person or organization and usually transmitted by mail.

label: magazine
desc: A periodical of magazine Articles. A magazine is a publication that is issued periodically, usually bound in a paper cover, and typically contains essays, stories, poems, etc., by many writers, and often photographs and drawings, frequently specializing in a particular subject or area, as hobbies, news, or sports.

label: manual
desc: A small reference book, especially one giving instructions.

label: manuscript
desc: An unpublished Document, which may also be submitted to a publisher for publication.

label: map
desc: A graphical depiction of geographic features.

label: multivolume book
desc: A loose, thematic, collection of Documents, often Books.

label: series
desc: A loose, thematic, collection of Documents, often Books.

label: newspaper
desc: A periodical of documents, usually issued daily or weekly, containing current news, editorials, feature articles, and usually advertising.

label: note
desc: Notes or annotations about a resource.

label: patent
desc: A document describing the exclusive right granted by a government to an inventor to manufacture, use, or sell an invention for a certain number of years.

label: performance
desc: A public performance.

label: periodical
desc: A group of related documents issued at regular intervals.

label: personal communication
desc: A communication between an agent and one or more specific recipients.

label: personal communication document
desc: A personal communication manifested in some document.

label: proceedings
desc: A compilation of documents published from an event, such as a conference.

label: quote
desc: An excerpted collection of words.

label: reference source
desc: A document that presents authoritative reference information, such as a dictionary or encylopedia .

label: report
desc: A document describing an account or statement describing in detail an event, situation, or the like, usually as the result of observation, inquiry, etc..

label: slide
desc: A slide in a slideshow

label: slideshow
desc: A presentation of a series of slides, usually presented in front of an audience with written text and images.

label: specification
desc: A document describing a specification.

label: standard
desc: A document describing a standard: a specification organized through a standards body.

label: statute
desc: A bill enacted into law.

label: thesis
desc: A document created to summarize research findings associated with the completion of an academic degree.

label: thesis degree
desc: The academic degree of a Thesis

label: webpage
desc: A web page is an online document available (at least initially) on the world wide web. A web page is written first and foremost to appear on the web, as distinct from other online resources such as books, manuscripts or audio documents which use the web primarily as a distribution mechanism alongside other more traditional methods such as print.

label: website
desc: A group of Webpages accessible on the Web.

label: workshop
desc: A seminar, discussion group, or the like, that emphasizes zxchange of ideas and the demonstration and application of techniques, skills, etc.

label: m.a.
desc: masters degree in arts

label: m.s.
desc: masters degree in science

label: phd degree
desc: PhD degree

label: accepted
desc: Accepted for publication after peer reviewing.

label: draft
desc: Document drafted

label: forthcoming
desc: Document to be published

label: legal
desc: Legal document

label: non peer reviewed
desc: A document that is not peer reviewed

label: peer reviewed
desc: The process by which articles are chosen to be included in a refereed journal. An editorial board consisting of experts in the same field as the author review the article and decide if it is authoritative enough for publication.

label: published
desc: Published document

label: rejected
desc: Rejected for publication after peer reviewing.

label: unpublished
desc: Unpublished document

label: agent
desc: A resource that acts or has the power to act.

label: agent class
desc: A group of agents.

label: bibliographic resource
desc: A book, article, or other documentary resource.

label: dcmi box
desc: The set of regions in space defined by their geographic coordinates according to the DCMI Box Encoding Scheme.

label: dcmi type vocabulary
desc: The set of classes specified by the DCMI Type Vocabulary, used to categorize the nature or genre of the resource.

label: ddc
desc: The set of conceptual resources specified by the Dewey Decimal Classification.

label: file format
desc: A digital resource format.

label: frequency
desc: A rate at which something recurs.

label: imt
desc: The set of media types specified by the Internet Assigned Numbers Authority.

label: iso 3166
desc: The set of codes listed in ISO 3166-1 for the representation of names of countries.

label: iso 639-2
desc: The three-letter alphabetic codes listed in ISO639-2 for the representation of names of languages.

label: iso 639-3
desc: The set of three-letter codes listed in ISO 639-3 for the representation of names of languages.

label: jurisdiction
desc: The extent or range of judicial, law enforcement, or other authority.

label: lcc
desc: The set of conceptual resources specified by the Library of Congress Classification.

label: lcsh
desc: The set of labeled concepts specified by the Library of Congress Subject Headings.

label: license document
desc: A legal document giving official permission to do something with a Resource.

label: linguistic system
desc: A system of signs, symbols, sounds, gestures, or rules used in communication.

label: location
desc: A spatial region or named place.

label: location, period, or jurisdiction
desc: A location, period of time, or jurisdiction.

label: mesh
desc: The set of labeled concepts specified by the Medical Subject Headings.

label: media type
desc: A file format or physical medium.

label: media type or extent
desc: A media type or extent.

label: method of accrual
desc: A method by which resources are added to a collection.

label: method of instruction
desc: A process that is used to engender knowledge, attitudes, and skills.

label: nlm
desc: The set of conceptual resources specified by the National Library of Medicine Classification.

label: dcmi period
desc: The set of time intervals defined by their limits according to the DCMI Period Encoding Scheme.

label: period of time
desc: An interval of time that is named or defined by its start and end dates.

label: physical medium
desc: A physical material or carrier.

label: physical resource
desc: A material thing.

label: dcmi point
desc: The set of points in space defined by their geographic coordinates according to the DCMI Point Encoding Scheme.

label: policy
desc: A plan or course of action by an authority, intended to influence and determine decisions, actions, and other matters.

label: provenance statement
desc: A statement of any changes in ownership and custody of a resource since its creation that are significant for its authenticity, integrity, and interpretation.

label: rfc 1766
desc: The set of tags, constructed according to RFC 1766, for the identification of languages.

label: rfc 3066
desc: The set of tags constructed according to RFC 3066 for the identification of languages.

label: rfc 4646
desc: The set of tags constructed according to RFC 4646 for the identification of languages.

label: rfc 5646
desc: The set of tags constructed according to RFC 5646 for the identification of languages.

label: rights statement
desc: A statement about the intellectual property rights (IPR) held in or over a Resource, a legal document giving official permission to do something with a resource, or a statement about access rights.

label: size or duration
desc: A dimension or extent, or a time taken to play or execute.

label: standard
desc: A basis for comparison; a reference point against which other things can be evaluated.

label: tgn
desc: The set of places specified by the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names.

label: udc
desc: The set of conceptual resources specified by the Universal Decimal Classification.

label: uri
desc: The set of identifiers constructed according to the generic syntax for Uniform Resource Identifiers as specified by the Internet Engineering Task Force.

label: w3c-dtf
desc: The set of dates and times constructed according to the W3C Date and Time Formats Specification.

label: abstract
desc: A summary of the resource.

label: access rights
desc: Information about who can access the resource or an indication of its security status.

label: accrual method
desc: The method by which items are added to a collection.

label: accrual periodicity
desc: The frequency with which items are added to a collection.

label: accrual policy
desc: The policy governing the addition of items to a collection.

label: alternative title
desc: An alternative name for the resource.

label: audience
desc: A class of entity for whom the resource is intended or useful.

label: date available
desc: Date (often a range) that the resource became or will become available.

label: bibliographic citation
desc: A bibliographic reference for the resource.

label: conforms to
desc: An established standard to which the described resource conforms.

label: contributor
desc: An entity responsible for making contributions to the resource.

label: coverage
desc: The spatial or temporal topic of the resource, the spatial applicability of the resource, or the jurisdiction under which the resource is relevant.

label: date created
desc: Date of creation of the resource.

label: creator
desc: An entity primarily responsible for making the resource.

label: date
desc: A point or period of time associated with an event in the lifecycle of the resource.

label: date accepted
desc: Date of acceptance of the resource.

label: date copyrighted
desc: Date of copyright.

label: date submitted
desc: Date of submission of the resource.

label: description
desc: An account of the resource.

label: audience education level
desc: A class of entity, defined in terms of progression through an educational or training context, for which the described resource is intended.

label: extent
desc: The size or duration of the resource.

label: format
desc: The file format, physical medium, or dimensions of the resource.

label: has format
desc: A related resource that is substantially the same as the pre-existing described resource, but in another format.

label: has part
desc: A related resource that is included either physically or logically in the described resource.

label: has version
desc: A related resource that is a version, edition, or adaptation of the described resource.

label: identifier
desc: An unambiguous reference to the resource within a given context.

label: instructional method
desc: A process, used to engender knowledge, attitudes and skills, that the described resource is designed to support.

label: is format of
desc: A related resource that is substantially the same as the described resource, but in another format.

label: is part of
desc: A related resource in which the described resource is physically or logically included.

label: is referenced by
desc: A related resource that references, cites, or otherwise points to the described resource.

label: is replaced by
desc: A related resource that supplants, displaces, or supersedes the described resource.

label: is required by
desc: A related resource that requires the described resource to support its function, delivery, or coherence.

label: is version of
desc: A related resource of which the described resource is a version, edition, or adaptation.

label: date issued
desc: Date of formal issuance (e.g., publication) of the resource.

label: language
desc: A language of the resource.

label: license
desc: A legal document giving official permission to do something with the resource.

label: mediator
desc: An entity that mediates access to the resource and for whom the resource is intended or useful.

label: medium
desc: The material or physical carrier of the resource.

label: date modified
desc: Date on which the resource was changed.

label: provenance
desc: A statement of any changes in ownership and custody of the resource since its creation that are significant for its authenticity, integrity, and interpretation.

label: publisher
desc: An entity responsible for making the resource available.

label: references
desc: A related resource that is referenced, cited, or otherwise pointed to by the described resource.

label: relation
desc: A related resource.

label: replaces
desc: A related resource that is supplanted, displaced, or superseded by the described resource.

label: requires
desc: A related resource that is required by the described resource to support its function, delivery, or coherence.

label: rights
desc: Information about rights held in and over the resource.

label: rights holder
desc: A person or organization owning or managing rights over the resource.

label: source
desc: A related resource from which the described resource is derived.

label: spatial coverage
desc: Spatial characteristics of the resource.

label: subject
desc: The topic of the resource.

label: table of contents
desc: A list of subunits of the resource.

label: temporal coverage
desc: Temporal characteristics of the resource.

label: title
desc: A name given to the resource.

label: type
desc: The nature or genre of the resource.

label: date valid
desc: Date (often a range) of validity of a resource.

label: preferred label
desc: A resource has no more than one value of skos:prefLabel per language tag, and no more than one value of skos:prefLabel without language tag.

label: preferred label
desc: The range of skos:prefLabel is the class of RDF plain literals.

label: preferred label
desc:
skos:prefLabel, skos:altLabel and skos:hiddenLabel are pairwise
      disjoint properties.

label: alternative label
desc: The range of skos:altLabel is the class of RDF plain literals.

label: alternative label
desc: skos:prefLabel, skos:altLabel and skos:hiddenLabel are pairwise disjoint properties.

label: hidden label
desc: skos:prefLabel, skos:altLabel and skos:hiddenLabel are pairwise disjoint properties.

label: hidden label
desc: The range of skos:hiddenLabel is the class of RDF plain literals.

label: has broader
desc: Broader concepts are typically rendered as parents in a concept hierarchy (tree).

label: has narrower
desc: Narrower concepts are typically rendered as children in a concept hierarchy (tree).

label: has related
desc: skos:related is disjoint with skos:broaderTransitive

label: has member list
desc:
For any resource, every item in the list given as the value of the
      skos:memberList property is also a value of the skos:member property.

label: is in mapping relation with
desc: These concept mapping relations mirror semantic relations, and the data model defined below is similar (with the exception of skos:exactMatch) to the data model defined for semantic relations. A distinct vocabulary is provided for concept mapping relations, to provide a convenient way to differentiate links within a concept scheme from links between concept schemes. However, this pattern of usage is not a formal requirement of the SKOS data model, and relies on informal definitions of best practice.

label: has exact match
desc: skos:exactMatch is disjoint with each of the properties skos:broadMatch and skos:relatedMatch.
